@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<main class="container">
    <hgroup>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p>Because even notes-sharing apps need rules</p>
    </hgroup>

    <article>
        <h2>1. We Respect Your Notes</h2>
        <p>
            Your notes are yours. We don't peek… unless your note says "Delete me after reading" — in that case, we
            obey.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2>2. No Creepy Tracking</h2>
        <p>
            We don't track your IP like a hawk. We only store what's needed to deliver your note — kind of like your
            nosy neighbor who just waves politely.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2>3. Custom Codes</h2>
        <p>
            You can choose your own code for your notes. Just don't pick "1234" — that's boring. And yes, we'll tell you
            if your custom code is already taken 😂.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2>4. Self-Destructing Notes</h2>
        <p>
            If you tick "Delete after view", we will self-destruct the note like a mini-movie explosion. Refreshing
            the page means it's gone.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
            We don't use cookies for spying. Only the ones necessary for keeping your session alive. Feel free to
            dunk them in milk.
        </p>
    </article>
</main>